## How to read this list

Each row represents a third-party service that may process information
collected through {{PROJECT_NAME}}. PIPEDA Principle 1 makes us
accountable; FINTRAC's reporting-entity expectations make AML-relevant
vendor relationships subject to additional scrutiny.

| Column | Meaning |
|---|---|
| **Vendor** | Legal name + service. |
| **Function** | What the vendor does for us. |
| **Data category** | What classes of information they process. |
| **Region** | Where the processing occurs. |
| **DPA** | Data-processing agreement in place. |
| **Audit evidence** | SOC 2 Type II, SOC 1 Type II, ISO 27001, or other independent attestation. |
| **AML scope** | Is this vendor part of the AML/sanctions pipeline? |
| **Notes** | Anything material. |

